Hey, just a quick question about an issue I'm having:

First off I want to say, amazing mod. I love the engines so much. But, I have an issue with most launchers. When I decouple the first stage the second stage decides to randomly explode for no reason. I'm using Kerbal Joint Reinforcement so could that be part of the issue or not? Thanks for your help.

40 minutes ago, nathan98900 said:

Hey, just a quick question about an issue I'm having:

First off I want to say, amazing mod. I love the engines so much. But, I have an issue with most launchers. When I decouple the first stage the second stage decides to randomly explode for no reason. I'm using Kerbal Joint Reinforcement so could that be part of the issue or not? Thanks for your help.

Are you using the KSP 1.0.4 version? It contains the Atlas, Deltas, an earlier version of the Falcon 1 and the Minotaur V. That version has concave colliders, so if you try to decouple stages and/or fairings in KSP 1.0.5, things will explode.

Currently the SpaceX LVP (Falcon 1, Falcon 9 v1.0, v1.1, v1.2, and Falcon Heavy) is the only pack that is compatible with KSP 1.0.5.

Edited January 20, 2016 by Delta_8930

Just so you know, the Falcon 9 V1.0 upper stage has something like 4000 liquid fuel. The rocket barely gets off the ground.
The upper stage is supposed to have a lot of fuel and operate for a long time, just like IRL. It operates for 6 minutes and can still deliver payloads to orbit, albeit at a slower rate.
